# Rule: .github/CODEOWNERS

The file uses GitHub's `CODEOWNERS` syntax (one path glob per line, then
`@org/team` or `@user`). The `check:md` script considers this a `.md`
(tracked because of extension) but does **not** validate syntax — GitHub
itself reports parse errors.

For the bootstrap PR there is a single owner (the project lead). As the
project grows, the file moves toward per-package ownership, e.g.:

```
/packages/supervisor/  @hookorama/supervisor-maintainers
/packages/client/      @hookorama/client-maintainers
/AGENTS.md             @hookorama/governance-maintainers
```

The default reviewer set must **never** be empty; if a path is not
covered, code there merges without review.
